  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The impact of Baby-friendly Hospital Initiative (BFHI) to breastfeeding, breastfeeding
      counselling and breastfeeding attitudes will be examined in Satakunta Central Hospital,
      Finland. The baseline measurement will be conducted before the implementation of BFHI in 2017
      and second measurement will be conducted in 2019 after the certification process. Both staff
      members and breastfeeding mothers will be recruited in the study. The main outcomes are the
      duration of breastfeeding and breastfeeding attitudes.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
